<item>
            <title>[LUDOC-61] lfs setstripe documentation should cover inactive or degraded OSTs</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-61</link>
                <project id="10070" key="LUDOC">Lustre Documentation</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This is a dup of lustre.bugzilla.org bug # 24477&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;From that bug:&lt;br/&gt;
The lfs setstripe documentation in the Lustre Operations Manual (Section 28.1 of the 1.8 manual)&lt;br/&gt;
does not address when the specified starting OST or round-robin nature of stripe allocation will&lt;br/&gt;
not be honored because OSTs are inactive or in a degraded mode.  The doc should be updated because&lt;br/&gt;
the MDS will choose other candidates silently without informing the user.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The documentation could read, &quot;In some cases the desired OST(s) can not be used because an OST is&lt;br/&gt;
inactive or in a degraded mode.  In that case the MDS will silently choose another target.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;#8211;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The pertinent section in the 2.x manual is 18.3.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
